### LNURLw Server Test Requests

# Set variables
@baseUrl = https://lnurlw.sirion.io
@domain = lnurlw.sirion.io

### 1. Create a new bolt card
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/createboltcard
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "card_name": "Test Card 1",
  "tx_limit_sats": 50000,
  "day_limit_sats": 500000,
  "enabled": true
}

### 2. Create another card with minimal config
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/createboltcard
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "card_name": "Basic Card"
}

### 3. Get card registration info (replace 'YOUR_ONE_TIME_CODE' with actual code from step 1 response)
GET {{baseUrl}}/new?a=e6c8971ca5bae188233c523bf6869c37

### 4. Test LNURLw endpoint with dummy data (this will fail validation but shows the error handling)
GET {{baseUrl}}/ln?card_id=1&p=1234567890abcdef1234567890abcdef&c=1234567890abcdef

### 5. Test LNURLw callback with dummy data (this will also fail but shows error handling)
GET {{baseUrl}}/ln/callback?k1=dummy_k1&pr=lnbc1000n1p1234567890

### Example flow after card creation:
# 1. Run the "Create a new bolt card" request
# 2. Copy the one_time_code from the "url" field in the response
# 3. Replace YOUR_ONE_TIME_CODE in step 3 with the actual code
# 4. Run the registration request to get the card keys for NFC programming

### Health check (optional - server doesn't implement this but shows 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/health